```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([Administrator navigates to login page]) --> Enter[Administrator enters email and password]
    Enter --> Click[Administrator clicks Login button]
    Click --> Send[Frontend sends POST /api/auth/login]
    Send --> Receive[Backend receives request]
    Receive --> Query[Backend queries MongoDB for user by email]
    
    Query --> CheckUser{User exists in database?}
    CheckUser -->|No| Error1[Return 401 Unauthorized<br/>Incorrect email or password]
    Error1 --> Display1[Frontend displays error message]
    Display1 --> End1([End])
    
    CheckUser -->|Yes| Verify[Backend verifies password with bcrypt]
    Verify --> CheckPass{Password matches hash?}
    CheckPass -->|No| Error2[Return 401 Unauthorized<br/>Incorrect email or password]
    Error2 --> Display2[Frontend displays error message]
    Display2 --> End2([End])
    
    CheckPass -->|Yes| UpdateLogin[Backend updates last_login timestamp]
    UpdateLogin --> CheckRole[Backend validates user role]
    CheckRole --> CheckAdmin{User role is Admin?}
    CheckAdmin -->|No| Error3[Return 403 Forbidden<br/>Administrator access only]
    Error3 --> Display3[Frontend displays error message]
    Display3 --> End3([End])
    
    CheckAdmin -->|Yes - Admin| CreateToken[Backend creates JWT tokens<br/>Access: 30 min, Refresh: 7 days]
    CreateToken --> ReturnTokens[Backend returns tokens to frontend]
    ReturnTokens --> StoreTokens[Frontend stores tokens in Zustand<br/>with localStorage persistence]
    StoreTokens --> GetProfile[Frontend calls GET /api/auth/me<br/>with Bearer token]
    GetProfile --> StoreUser[Store user profile in Zustand state]
    StoreUser --> Redirect[Frontend redirects to Dashboard]
    Redirect --> Success([Administrator sees dashboard<br/>with device list and statistics])
    
